o the temple and agro just a few Amys at a time, letting you survive the HTs without Harmshield or another DA type spell. Just one thing: VERY carefully... take one step too far and you're dead, and it doesn't seem to work from all directions. <br><br>The advantage of this is that with care the temple can be split even if you don't have a necro. However, it takes a lot longer as the puller has to be very careful, and will probably still die a few times even then - so a skilled necro definitely works best.<br><br>[Edit] I honestly would not consider the method described by Istrahd as an exploit. The mobs can still get to you, just by warping instead of running. If they had to actually run out of the temple it would be even easier to split than it is now when they warp, so I don't see a problem. All mobs, even in an open area, will usally string out in a line if you pull a large amount of them. <p>Ulaian Moonleaf <BR>-Warder <BR>Dark Whispers</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uulaian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ulaian</A> at: 1/21/02 8:57:12 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/unumruk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Numruk</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.student.nada.kth.se/~md96-jma/eq/canada.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/21/02 11:58:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumnecromancer.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=542.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www3.sympatico.ca/palad/smallskel.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I promised Neesha - Pulling PoF Temple Notes</span